name: Cincinnati Reds vs. Los Angeles Dodgers
Hamilton (NY)
pleaseNote: At this performance, masks are optional. Guests are strongly encouraged to wear masks in the theatre. Everyone who enters the theatre will need to comply with the most current COVID-19 policies on the day of the performance. Review all of the theatre policies: here.

accessibility.info:
Accessible seating is available for this performance as indicated on the seating map.

Wheelchair locations are available in the orchestra section of the theatre (pending availability). You may purchase one wheelchair and three companion seats per order if available.

For guests with limited mobility, there are seats available with folding armrests ("Aisle transfer seats") in these locations: Orchestra (no stairs): A1, A2, A101, C113, E1, E2, E23, E24, F101, F113; Orchestra (stairs required) L1, L2, M1, M2.

For low vision/deaf & hard of hearing guests, accessible seats are available in the Orchestra B 1-7 and B 2-8.

For more details on accessible seating policies please contact the box office directly by calling 212-221-1211.

ticketLimit.info: There is an 8 ticket limit per order. Maximum aggregate ticket limit for performances 4/4/23 - 9/3/23 is 8 tickets.

venues.name: Richard Rodgers Theatre

boxOfficeInfo.willCallDetail: Pick up tickets one hour prior to the show. Customers must present the actual credit card used to place the order and a photo ID.

venues.parkingDetail: Several lots are located within one block of the theatre. ParkWhiz https://www.parkwhiz.com/richard-rodgers-theatre-parking/

generalInfo.childRule: All persons entering the theatre, regardless of age, must have a ticket. Children under the age of 4 are not permitted in the theatre.

ada.adaCustomCopy: Accessible seating is available on Ticketmaster.com. For any questions about accessible seating you may contact the box office at 212-221-1211 or visit www.richardrodgerstheatre.com for more information.

name: Harry Potter and the Cursed Child - Parts 1 & 2 Fri 14:00 & 19:00

venues.name: Palace Theatre

boxOfficeInfo.openHoursDetail: Monday - Saturday 10:00 - 18:00 and occasionally on Sunday.
boxOfficeInfo.willCallDetail: Tickets left at the box office for collection may be picked up on the day, during the hour before the performance starts. Please take the credit card used to make the booking and the Ticketmaster booking reference number as proof of purchase.

venues.parkingDetail: National car park at St.Martins Lane. Street parking very difficult. Strongly advise public transport.
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: Infra red hearing system with no deposit required. For special needs seating please call 0844 412 4648. Disabled toilet situated in the rear Stalls with ground level access There is no limit to the amount of Guide Dogs (within reason of course)

generalInfo.generalRule: No video cameras or recording devices.
generalInfo.childRule: Babies and toddlers are not generally admitted into the theatre. Children must be able to sit, unaided, in their own seat and be attentive to the performance so as not to distract other paying members of the audience. As a GENERAL guideline an age of 5+ is recommended â€“ other age restrictions such as Parental Guidance may also apply with regards to the content of the production. Admittance to the auditorium is always at the discretion of the theatre management. This information applies to all Really Useful Theatres.

ada.adaPhones: Palace Theatre: 0844 482 9677 Calls will cost 7 ppm plus your network access charge.
ada.adaCustomCopy:
To better accommodate your needs, Palace Theatre has requested that all special seating accommodations be solicited only through their representatives. Please contact a Palace Theatre representative for further help with your ticket purchase.*   Advance ticket purchase may be required.

* Box office information is subject to change.

venues.name: Stadium of Light
venues.parkingDetail: There is a Park and Ride scheme on matchdays that is free to both home and away supporters. The scheme runs from the Sunderland Enterprise Park on the Wessington Way (A1231), which is easily accessible from the A19 and is clearly signposted "Park and Ride". Buses run every 5 minutes before the match and regularly afterwards until all supporters have been transported back to their cars.

ada.adaCustomCopy:
Ticketmaster are not selling Accessible tickets for this event.

To book tickets, please visit the Venues website via https://www.safc.com/concerts (copy to browser) for further information including parking.

For BSL requests, please contact:
https://www.eticketing.co.uk/safc/Hospitality/LandingPage (copy to browser)
